{"title_page": "VTV3", "text_new": "{{For|Virtual TV, Pakistan|Virtual University of Pakistan#Distant teaching}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Unreferenced|date=November 2016}}\n{{Notability|Television|date=November 2016}}\n}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n| name           = VTV3\n| logofile       = VTV3 logo 2013 final.svg\n| logosize       = 140px\n| launch         = {{Start date and age|1996|03|31}}\n| owner          = [[Vietnam Television]]\n| country        = [[Vietnam]]\n| sister names   = [[VTV1]], [[VTV2]], [[VTV4]], [[VTV5]], [[VTV6]], VTV7, VTV8 and VTV9\n| picture format = [[1080i]] [[HDTV]]<br />{{small|(downscaled to [[16:9]] [[576i]] for the [[SDTV]] feed)}}\n| broadcast area = [[Vietnam]]<br>[[Asia]]<br>Worldwide\n| share          = \n| share as of    = \n| share source   = \n| web            = \n| terr serv 1    = [[Analogue television in Vietnam|Vietnamese Analogue]]\n| terr chan 1    = VHF 6 in [[Hanoi]]\n| sat serv 1     = K+\n| sat chan 1     = CH.8 (HD)<br>CH.212 (SD)\n| sat serv 2     = MobiTV\n| sat chan 2     = CH.7 (HD)\n| sat serv 3     = VTC Digital\n| sat chan 3     = CH.14 (HD)\n| sat serv 4     = Vinasat (Cband)\n| sat chan 4     = (SD)\n| cable avail    = \n| cable serv 1   = [[VTVCab]]\n| cable chan 1   = CH.3 (HD) Analog CH.30 (SD)\n| cable serv 2   = SCTV\n| cable chan 2   = CH.23 (SD)<br>CH.232 (HD)\n| cable serv 3   = Hanoicab\n| cable chan 3   = CH.23 (SD)<br>CH.232 (HD)\n| cable serv 4   = [[Vietcable]]\n| cable chan 4   = Channel 3\n| adsl avail     = \n| adsl serv 1    = MyTV\n| adsl chan 1    = CH.3 (HD)<br>K\u00eanh 13 (SD)\n| adsl serv 2    = Viettel TV\n| adsl chan 2    = CH.4 (HD)\n| adsl serv 3    = FPT TV\n| adsl chan 3    = CH.3 (HD)\n| online avail   = \n| online serv 1  = VTVGo\n| online chan 1  = \n| online serv 2  = VTV.vn\n| online chan 2  = [https://vtv.vn/truyen-hinh-truc-tuyen/vtv3.htm Watch live]\n| online serv 3  = VTV Entertainment\n| online chan 3  = [https://www.vtvgiaitri.vn/xem-tivi-truc-tuyen/vtv3 Watch live]\n| online serv 4  = FPT Play\n| online chan 4  = [https://fptplay.vn/livetv/vtv3-hd Watch live]\n| online serv 5  = TV Net ([[Vietnam Television Corporation|VTC]])\n| online chan 5  = [http://vn.tvnet.gov.vn/kenh-truyen-hinh/1013/vtv3 Watch live]\n}}\n'''VTV3''' is a Vietnamese television station operated and owned by government-owned [[Vietnam Television|VTV Network]]. It launched on 31 March 1996 and has broadcast for 19/7 since 19 March 2020 as the country's first sports and entertainment channel, as well as American and Asian series.\n\n== Broadcast ==\n* VTV3 was broadcast by Vietnam Television for testing, the remaining programs will be broadcast at the same frequency range of [[VTV1]] and [[VTV2]], with the content is Sports - Entertainment and Economic Information. The channel was broadcast in channel 6 in Hanoi. Broadcast time was from 6:00 p.m to 12:00 a.m. The channel began to be relayed nationwide via satellite on 31 March 1998.\n\n* Until 31 December 2001:\n** From Monday to Friday: 12:00 p.m to 12:00 a.m\n** Saturday and Sunday: 10:00 a.m to 12:00 a.m\n* From 31 December 2001 to 5 August 2006: 6:00 a.m to 12:00 a.m\n* From 1 September 2006 to 18 March 2020: 24/7.\n* From 19 March 2020 to 15 April 2020: 5:00a.m to 12:00a.m\n* Since 16 April 2020 (since 20 April and since 01 May 2020): 24/7 (to the end of coronavirus season the end of quarantine isolations).\n\n== VTV3 HD ==\nVTV3 become the first channel of VTV and the first commercial television channel in Vietnam to have an HD simulcast. '''VTV3 HD''' was soft-launched from 31 March 2013 to mark VTV3 17th anniversary and officially launched on 1 June 2013.{{citation needed|date=November 2016}} Most of programs broadcast by VTV3 since 2013 are in HDTV with 16:9 picture format.\n\n== List of programs currently broadcast by VTV3 ==\n\n*'''''C\u00e0 ph\u00ea s\u00e1ng v\u1edbi VTV3'''''\n*'''''Drama, Flim'''''\n*'''''Ch\u1ecdn \u0111\u00e2u cho \u0111\u00fang - The Crush'''''\n*'''''Ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u0111i xuy\u00ean t\u01b0\u1eddng - Hole in The Wall'''''\n*'''''Ai l\u00e0 tri\u1ec7u ph\u00fa - Who Wants To Be A Millionaire''' \n*'''''Kh\u00f4ng gi\u1edbi h\u1ea1n - Sasuke Vietnam'''''\n*'''''Ch\u1ecdn ngay \u0111i - The Best Of All'''''\n*'''''Vui - Kho\u1ebb - C\u00f3 \u00edch (November 2004 - present)'''''\n*'''''\u0110\u01b0\u1eddng l\u00ean \u0111\u1ec9nh Olympia'''''\n*'''''Chuy\u1ec7n \u0111\u00eam mu\u1ed9n'''''\n*'''''G\u01b0\u01a1ng m\u1eb7t th\u00e2n quen - [[Your Face Sounds Familiar]]'' (5 January 2013 - 18 January 2020)'''\n*'''''Qu\u1ea3 c\u1ea7u b\u00ed \u1ea9n - Boom! (Since 3 March 2019)'''''\n*'''''[[Shark Tank|Th\u01b0\u01a1ng v\u1ee5 b\u1ea1c t\u1ef7]] - Shark Tank Vietnam (since November 2017)'''''\n*'''''V\u01b0\u1ee3t th\u00e0nh chi\u1ebfn - Block Out '''''\n*'''''G\u00e0 \u0111\u1ebb tr\u1ee9ng v\u00e0ng'''''\n*'''''[[Singer Auction|S\u00e0n chi\u1ebfn gi\u1ecdng h\u00e1t - Singer Auction]] (since 19 July 2019)'''''\n*'''''\u01a0n gi\u1eddi c\u1eadu \u0111\u00e2y r\u1ed3i - Thank Got You Are Here (since October 2014)'''''\n*'''''K\u00fd \u1ee9c vui v\u1ebb - De Generatie Show'''''\n*'''''Gi\u00e1c quan th\u1ee9 6'''''\n\n'''''Details:'''''\n[[:vi:Danh s\u00e1ch c\u00e1c ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh ph\u00e1t s\u00f3ng c\u1ee7a \u0110\u00e0i Truy\u1ec1n h\u00ecnh Vi\u1ec7t Nam|List of broadcasts of Vietnam Television (VTV)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* [[:vi:Danh s\u00e1ch c\u00e1c ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\u00ecnh ph\u00e1t s\u00f3ng c\u1ee7a \u0110\u00e0i Truy\u1ec1n h\u00ecnh Vi\u1ec7t Nam|List of broadcasts of Vietnam Television (VTV)]]\n\n{{VTV}}\n[[Category:Vietnam Television]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Sports television networks]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese television networks]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|Virtual TV, Pakistan|Virtual University of Pakistan#Distant teaching}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Unreferenced|date=November 2016}}\n{{Notability|Television|date=November 2016}}\n}}\n{{Infobox TV chan