''\n|David Dvorkin\n|June 1988\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-64870-5}}\n|-\n|41\n|''The Three-Minute Universe''\n|Barbara Paul\n|August 1988\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65816-6}}\n|-\n|42\n|''Memory Prime'' \u2021\n|Judith and Garfield Reeves-Stevens\n|October 1988\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65813-1}}\n|-\n|43\n|''The Final Nexus''\n|Gene DeWeese\n|December 1988\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-66018-7}}\n|-\n|44\n|''Vulcan's Glory''\n|D. C. Fontana\n|February 1989\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65667-8}}\n|-\n|45\n|''Double, Double''\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|April 1989\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-66130-2}}\n|-\n|46\n|''The Cry of the Onlies''\n|Judy Klass\n|October 1989\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-68167-2}}\n|-\n|47\n|''The Kobayashi Maru''{{Hsp}}{{Efn-lr|Similarly named novels:{{Blist|''The Kobayashi Maru'' (''{{Teal|Star Trek}}'', Book 47) (1989), by [[Julia Ecklar]].|''Kobayashi Maru'' (''{{Teal|Enterprise}}''{{--)}} (2008), novel by [[Michael A. Martin]] and [[Andy Mangels]].}}|name=kobayashi}}\n|Julia Ecklar\n|December 1989\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65817-4}}\n|-\n|48\n|''Rules of Engagement''\n|Peter Morwood\n|February 1990\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-66129-9}}\n|-\n|49\n|''The Pandora Principle''\n|Carolyn Clowes\n|April 1990\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65815-8}}\n|-\n|50\n|''Doctor's Orders''\n|Diane Duane\n|June 1990\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-66189-2}}\n|-\n|51\n|''Enemy Unseen''\n|V.E. Mitchell\n|October 1990\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-68403-5}}\n|-\n|52\n|''Home Is the Hunter''\n|Dana Kramer-Rolls\n|December 1990\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-66662-2}}\n|-\n|53\n|''Ghost-Walker''\n|Barbara Hambly\n|February 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-64398-3}}\n|-\n|54\n|''A Flag Full of Stars''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Lost Years}}'', Book 2)}}\n|Brad Ferguson{{Efn-lg|As by Brad Ferguson. Uncredited rewrite completed by J.M. Dillard.|name=flag}}\n|April 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-73918-2}}\n|-\n|55\n|''Renegade''\n|Gene DeWeese\n|June 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65814-X}}\n|-\n|56\n|''Legacy''\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|August 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-74468-2}}\n|-\n|57\n|''The Rift''\n|Peter David\n|November 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-74796-7}}\n|-\