006\u20132009) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Mere Anarchy''''' miniseries explores the effects of an off-world disaster over a thirty-year period. Inspired by \"[[The Second Coming (poem)|The Second Coming]]\" by [[W. B. Yeats]]. Published as ebook exclusives. An omnibus edition was published in 2009.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title \u25ca\n!Author(s)\n!Date{{Efn|Exact date of release is not known, or not available via primary sources. Approximated to the nearest month.|name=streetdate}}\n!ISBN (ebook)\n|-\n|1\n|''Things Fall Apart''\n|Dayton Ward and Kevin Dilmore\n|August 2006\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-3437-7}}\n|-\n|2\n|''The Centre Cannot Hold''\n|Mike W. Barr\n|September 2006\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-3436-9}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Shadows of the Indignant''\n|Dave Galanter\n|October 2006\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-3453-9}}\n|-\n|4\n|''The Darkness Drops Again''\n|Christopher L. Bennett\n|February 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-3452-5}}\n|-\n|5\n|''The Blood-Dimmed Tide''\n|Howard Weinstein\n|March 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-3451-8}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Its Hour Come Round''\n|Margaret Wander Bonanno\n|April 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-3454-9}}\n|-\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|''Mere Anarchy'' (omnibus)\n|Keith DeCandido, ed.{{Efn-ua|''Mere Anarchy'' (2009) (''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}} by Keith DeCandido, editor, with Mike W. Barr, Christopher L. Bennett, Margaret Wander Bonanno, Dave Galanter, Dayton Ward, Kevin Gilmore, and Howard Weinstein.}}\n|March 17, 2009\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-9494-9}} (print){{Brk}}{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-5841-8}} (ebook)\n|}\n\n==== ''Crucible'' (2006\u201307) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Crucible''''' miniseries focused the experiences of [[Leonard McCoy|McCoy]], [[Spock]], and [[James T. Kirk|Kirk]]. Written by [[David R. George III]]. An omnibus edition, with new material, was announced in 2008, but was cancelled in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.trekbbs.com/threads/tentative-covers-descriptions-for-upcoming-summer-2009-trek-books.77931/|title=Tentative Covers & Descriptions for Upcoming 