|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 49)}}\n|September 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01922-8}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Double Helix'' (1999\u20132002) ====\n'''''Star Trek: The Next Generation'''{{Snd}}'''Double Helix''''' crossover miniseries was inspired by the film ''[[Outbreak (film)|Outbreak]]'' (1995).<ref name=\":0\" />{{Rp|434}} Created by [[John J. Ordover]] and [[Michael Jan Friedman]]. An omnibus edition was published in 2002. The series was published as part of the ''Next Generation'' book line based on recommendations from the sales team at Pocket Books.<ref name=\":0\" />{{Rp|434}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Infection''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 51)}}\n|John Gregory Betancourt\n| rowspan=\"2\" |June 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03255-0}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Vectors''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 52)}}\n|Dean Wesley Smith and Kristine Kathryn Rusch\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03256-9}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Red Sector''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 53)}}\n|Diane Carey\n| rowspan=\"2\" |July 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03257-7}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Quarantine''{{Hsp}}{{Efn-lr|name=quarantine}} \u2021{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 54)}}\n|John Vornholt\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03477-4}}\n|-\n|5\n|''Double or Nothing''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 55)}}\n|Peter David\n| rowspan=\"2\" |August 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03478-2}}\n|-\n|6\n|''The First Virtue''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}'', Book 56)}}\n|Michael Jan Friedman and Christie Golden\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03258-5}}\n|-\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|''Double Helix''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|Does not include the ''Next Generation'' subtitle.}} (omnibus)\n|John Gregory Betancourt, et al.{{Efn-ua|''Double Helix'' (''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}''{{--)}} (2002) by John Gregory Betancourt, Dean Wesley Smith and Kristine Kathryn Rusch, Diane Carey, John Vorhnolt, Peter David, and Michael Jan Friedman and Christie Golden.}}\n|October 8, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1272-9}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Genesis Wave'' (2000\u20132003) ====\n'''''Star Trek: The Next Generation'''{{Snd}}'''The Genesis Wave''''' miniseries follows the crew of the ''Enterprise'' as they attempt to prevent the weaponization of the Genesis Device. Written by [[John Vornholt]]. An omnibus edition collecting Books 1 and 2 was published by the Science Fiction Book Club in 2001.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title \u2020\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Genesis Wave'', Book 1\n| rowspan=\"4\" |John Vornholt\n|August 29, 2000\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1180-3}}\n|-\n|''The Genesis Wave'', Book 2\n|April 3, 2001\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1181-1}}\n|-\n|''The Genesis Wave'', Book 3\n|January 2, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-4375-6}}\n|-\n|''Genesis Force''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Genesis Wave}}'', Book 4)}}\n|June 18, 2003\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6503-2}}\n|}\n\n==== ''A Time to\u2026'' (2004) ====\n'''''Star Trek: A Time to...''''' miniseries explores events prior to ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis|Nemesis]]'' (2002). Conceived by John J. Ordover, and edited by [[Keith DeCandido]].<ref name=\":0\" />{{Rp|464}} Intended to be a sequence of twelve novels.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.psiphi.org/cgi/upc-db/new-200306.html|title=Psi Phi Star Trek Book Database: What's Old: February through June 2003|website=www.psiphi.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408210742/http://www.psiphi.org/cgi/upc-db/new-200306.html|archive-date=2016-04-08|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> The novels do not include the ''Next Generation'' subtitle. Not all printings include a number stamp.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''A Time to Be Born''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |John Vornholt\n|January 27, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6765-5}}\n|-\n|2\n|''A Time to Die''\n|February 24, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6766-3}}\n|-\n|3\n|''A Time to Sow''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Dayton Ward and Kevin Dilmore\n|March 30, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8299-9}}\n|-\n|4\n|''A Time to Harvest''\n|April 27, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8298-0}}\n|-\n|5\n|''A Time to Love''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Robert Greenberger\n|May 25, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6285-8}}\n|-\n|6\n|''A Time to Hate''\n|June 29, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6289-0}}\n|-\n|7\n|''A Time to Kill''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |David Mack\n|July 27, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9177-7}}\n|-\n|8\n|''A Time to Heal''\n|August 31, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9178-5}}\n|-\n|9\n|''A Time for War, a Time for Peace''\n|Keith DeCandido\n|September 28, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9179-3}}\n|}\n\n==== Relaunch novels (2005\u2013present) ====\nInterlinked novels set after the film ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis|Nemesis]]'' (2002):\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Death in Winter'' \u2020\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|September 20, 2005\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9721-X}}\n|-\n|''The Buried Age''\n|Christopher L. Bennett\n|June 26, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-3739-7}}\n|-\n|''Resistance''\n|J.M. Dillard\n|August 28, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7434-9955-2}}\n|-\n|''Q & A''\n|Keith DeCandido\n|September 25, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-2741-1}}\n|-\n|''The Sky's the Limit'' (anthology)\n|Marco Palmieri, ed.\n|October 16, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7434-9255-3}}\n|-\n|''Before Dishonor''\n|Peter David\n|October 30, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-2742-8}}\n|-\n|''Greater than the Sum''\n|Christopher L. Bennett\n|July 29, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-7132-2}}\n|-\n|''Losing the Peace''\n|William Leisner\n|June 30, 2009\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-0786-7}}\n|-\n|''Indistinguishable From Magic''\n|David A. McIntee\n|March 29, 2011\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-0615-7}}\n|-\n|''The Stuff of Dreams'' \u25ca\n|James Swallow\n|March 25, 2013\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-9661-5}}\n|-\n|''The Light Fantastic''\n|Jeffrey Lang\n|June 24, 2014\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-5051-4}}\n|-\n|''Q Are Cordially Uninvited\u2026'' \u25ca\n|Rudy Josephs\n|October 6, 2014\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-7882-2}}\n|-\n|''Takedown''\n|John Jackson Miller\n|January 27, 2015\n|{{I