-5073-0}}\n|-\n|3\n|''The Body Electric''\n|December 26, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-5074-7}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Deep Space Nine'' (1993\u20132017) ===\n{{Main|List of Star Trek: Deep Space Nine novels}}\n[[File:Star Trek DS9 logo.svg|thumb|alt=Star Trek: Deep Space Nine logo.]]\n'''''Star Trek: Deep Space Nine''''' book line is based on the [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine|television series of the same name]]. The book line was relaunched with the publication of ''Lives of Dax'' (2001), edited by Marco Palmieri.\n\n==== Episode novelizations (1993\u20131999) ====\nBased on select episodes from the television series. ''Call to Arms'' (1998) and ''Sacrifice of Angels'' (1998) are based on seven interlinked episodes from ''Deep Space Nine''{{'s}} [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine (season 5)|Seasons 5]] and [[Star Trek: Deep Space Nine (season 6)|6]], beginning with the episode \"[[Call to Arms (Star Trek: Deep Space Nine)|Call to Arms]]\".\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Emissary''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Deep Space Nine}}'', Book 1)}}\n|J.M. Dillard\n|February 1993\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-79858-8}}\n|-\n|''The Search''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Diane Carey\n|October 1994\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-50604-8}}\n|-\n|''The Way of the Warrior''\n|October 1995\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-56813-2}}\n|-\n|''Trials and Tribble-ations''\n|December 1996\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00902-8}}\n|-\n|''Far Beyond the Stars''\n|Steven Barnes\n|April 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02430-2}}\n|-\n|''Call to Arms''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Pink|The Dominion War}}'', Book 2)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Diane Carey\n|November 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02497-3}}\n|-\n|''Sacrifice of Angels''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Pink|The Dominion War}}'', Book 4)}}\n|December 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02498-1}}\n|-\n|''What You Leave Behind''\n|June 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03476-6}}\n|}\n\n==== Numbered novels (1993\u20132000) ====\nNumbered paperback releases:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Emissary''