ssion Gamma'' (2002) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Deep Space Nine'''{{Snd}}'''Mission Gamma''''' miniseries follows the crew of the {{Ship|USS|Defiant|wl=no}} under the command of Elias Vaughn. Not to be confused with the ''Gamma'' (2017), which has a similar premise. ''These Haunted Seas'' (2008) is a collection of Books 1 and 2.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Twilight'' \u2021\n|David R. George III\n| rowspan=\"2\" |August 27, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-4560-0}}\n|-\n|2\n|''This Gray Spirit'' \u2021\n|Heather Jarman\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-4562-7}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Cathedral''\n|Michael A. Martin and Andy Mangels\n|October 1, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-4564-3}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Lesser Evil''\n|Robert Simpson\n|October 29, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1024-6}}\n|-\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|''These Haunted Seas'' (omnibus){{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|Mission Gamma}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}2)}}\n|David R. George III and Heather Jarman\n|June 17, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-5639-8}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Worlds of Deep Space Nine'' (2004\u201305) ====\n'''''Worlds of Star Trek: Deep Space Nine''''' anthology series explores the various home worlds of the crew and residents of ''Deep Space Nine''. The series was created and edited by Marco Palmieri.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Cardassia and Andor''\n|Una McCormack and Heather Jarman\n|May 25, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8351-0}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Trill and Bajor''\n|Andy Mangels, Michael A. Martin, and J. Noah Kym\n| rowspan=\"2\" |January 25, 2005\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8352-9}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Ferenginar and The Dominion''\n|Keith DeCandido and David R. George III\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8353-7}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Terok Nor'' (2008) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Terok Nor''''' explores the history of the ''Deep Space Nine'' station during the [[Bajoran Occupation]], when it was known by its [[Cardassian]] name: ''Terok Nor''. The series is linked to ''The Lost Era'' (2003\u20132014). The book covers form a [[triptych]] by artist [[John Picacio]], and do not include the ''Deep Space Nine'' or the ''Lost Era'' subtitles.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Day of the Vipers''\n|James Swallow\n|March 25, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-5093-8}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Night of the Wolves''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |S. D. Perry and Britta Dennison\n|April 29, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7434-8251-6}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Dawn of the Eagles''\n|May 20, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7434-8252-3}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Gamma'' (2017) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Deep Space Nine'''{{Snd}}'''Gamma''''' miniseries follows the crew of {{Ship|USS|Robinson|wl=no}} under the command of [[Benjamin Sisko]]. Only one novel has been published. Not to be confused with the ''Mission Gamma'' (2002), which has a similar premise.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Original Sin''\n|David R. George III\n|September 26, 2017\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-3322-0}}\n|}\n\n=== Crossover novels (1994\u20132012) ===\n{{Anchor|Crossover novels}}\nCrossover novels and miniseries contain characters and settings from the various television series and films:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Federation'' \u2020\n|Judith and Garfield Reeves-Stevens\n|November 1994\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-89422-6}}\n|-\n|''The Badlands'', Book 1\n| rowspan=\"4\" |Susan Wright\n| rowspan=\"2\" |December 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03957-1}}\n|-\n|''The Badlands'', Book 2\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03958-X}}\n|-\n|''Dark Passions'', Book 1\n| rowspan=\"2\" |January 2, 2001\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-78785-3}}\n|-\n|''Dark Passions'', Book 2\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-78786-1}}\n|-\n|''Starfleet: Year One''\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|February 26, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-3788-8}}\n|-\n|''The Brave and the Bold'', Book 1\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Keith DeCandido\n| rowspan=\"2\" |November 26, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1922-7}}\n|-\n|''The Brave and the Bold'', Book 2\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1923-5}}\n|-\n|''Engines of Destiny''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|''Engin