ance of Shadows''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |David R. George III\n|August 29, 2006\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9168-8}}\n|-\n|''The Fire and the Rose''\n|November 28, 2006\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9169-6}}\n|-\n|''The Star to Every Wandering''\n|February 27, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7434-9170-9}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Legacies'' (2016) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Legacies''''' miniseries was published as part of ''Star Trek''{{'s}} 50th Anniversary celebration.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Captain to Captain''\n|Greg Cox\n|June 28, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-2529-4}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Best Defense''\n|David Mack\n|July 26, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-5310-2}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Purgatory's Key''\n|Dayton Ward and Kevin Dilmore\n|August 30, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-2277-4}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Next Generation'' (1988\u2013present) ===\n{{Main|List of Star Trek: The Next Generation novels}}\n[[File:Star Trek TNG logo.svg|thumb|alt=Star Trek: The Next Generation logo]]\n'''''Star Trek: The Next Generation''''' book line is based on the [[Star Trek: The Next Generation|television series of the same name]]. The book line was relaunched with the publication of ''Death in Winter'' (2005), by [[Michael Jan Friedman]].\n\n==== Episode novelizations (1987\u20131994) ====\nBased on select episodes from the television series.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Encounter at Farpoint''\n|David Gerrold\n|September 1987\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-65241-9}}\n|-\n|''Unification''\n|Jeri Taylor\n|December 1991\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-77056-X}}\n|-\n|''Relics''\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|November 1992\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-86476-9}}\n|-\n|''Descent''\n|Diane Carey\n|October 1993\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-88267-8}}\n|-\n|''All Good Things...'' \u2020\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|June 1994\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-71898-3}}\n|}\n\n==== Numbered novels (1988\u20132001) ====\nNumbered paperback releases:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Ghost Ship''\n|Dia