 Smith\n|February 26, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1926-X}}\n|-\n|''The Battle of Betazed''\n|Charlotte Douglas and Susan Kearney\n|April 2, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-3434-X}}\n|-\n|''Do Comets Dream?''\n|S. P. Somtow\n|June 6, 2003\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6500-8}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Starfleet Academy'' (1993\u20131998) ====\n'''''Star Trek: The Next Generation'''{{Snd}}'''Starfleet Academy''''' young adult miniseries explores the lives of the {{USS|Enterprise|NCC-1701-D|6}} crew as [[Starfleet Academy]] cadets. ''The Best and the Brightest'' (1998), by Susan Wright, is thematically similar. ''Starfleet Academy'' (1997), a video game novelization by Diane Carey, is unrelated.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title ^\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Worf's First Adventure''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Peter David\n|August 1993\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-87084-X}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Line of Fire''\n|October 1993\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-87085-8}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Survival''\n|December 1993\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-87086-6}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Capture the Flag''\n|John Vornholt\n|June 1994\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-87998-7}}\n|-\n|5\n|''Atlantis Station''\n|V.E. Mitchell\n|August 1994\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-88449-2}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Mystery of the Missing Crew''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Michael Jan Friedman\n|February 1995\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-50108-9}}\n|-\n|7\n|''Secret of the Lizard People''\n|April 1995\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-50109-7}}\n|-\n|8\n|''Starfall''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Brad and Barbara Strickland\n|October 1995\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-51010-X}}\n|-\n|9\n|''Nova Command''\n|December 1995\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-51009-6}}\n|-\n|10\n|''Loyalties''\n|Patricia Barnes-Svarney\n|April 1996\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-55280-5}}\n|-\n|11\n|''Crossfire''\n|John Vornholt\n|December 1996\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-55305-4}}\n|-\n|12\n|''Breakaway''\n|Bobbi J.G. Weiss and David Cody Weiss\n|April 1997\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00226-0}}\n|-\n|13\n|''The Haunted Starship''\n|Brad Ferguson\n|December 1997\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01432-3}}\n|-\n|14\n|''Deceptions''\n|Bobbi J.G. Weiss and David Cody Weiss\n|April 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0