and John J. Ordover. An omnibus edition was published in 1999. ''Treaty's Law'' is a ''Star Trek'' novel, but does not include the ''Original Series'' subtitle.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Ancient Blood''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Diane Carey\n| rowspan=\"2\" |September 1997\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00238-4}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Armageddon Sky''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Deep Space Nine}}''{{--)}}}}\n|L.A. Graf\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00675-4}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Her Klingon Soul''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Voyager}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n| rowspan=\"3\" |October 1997\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00240-6}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Treaty's Law''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Kristine Kathryn Rusch and Dean Wesley Smith\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-00424-7}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{Unknown|}}\n|''Honor Bound''{{Hsp}}{{Efn-lr|name=honor}}{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|Deep Space Nine}}'' (young adult), Book 11)}}\n|Diana G. Gallagher\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01452-8}}\n|-\n|''Day of Honor''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|name=day|Published as ''Day of Honor: The Television Episode''. The cover art is similar to other novels of the ''{{Pink|Day of Honor}}'' crossover miniseries.}} (novelization){{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Voyager}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|November 1997\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01981-3}}\n|-\n|''Day of Honor'' (omnibus)\n|Diane Carey, et al.{{Efn-ua|''Day of Honor'' (1999) by Diane Carey, L.A. Graf, Michael Jan Friedman, Dean Wesley Smith and Kristine Kathryn Rusch, and Diane G. Gallagher.}}\n|March 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02813-8}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Captain's Table'' (1998-2000) ====\n{{Anchor|The Captain's Table|Captain's Table}}\n'''''Star Trek: The Captain's Table''''' crossover miniseries is narrated by various starship captains during their visits to a trans-dimensional bar called The Captain's Table. An omnibus edition was published in 2000. A short story anthology of linked stories was published in 2005. ''War Dragons'' and ''Where Sea Meets Sky'' are ''Star Trek'' novels, but neither include the ''Original Series'' subtitle.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''War Dragons''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}}}}\n|L.A. Graf{{Efn-lg|name=kirksulu}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |June 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01463-3}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Dujonian's Hoard''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Michael Jan Friedman{{Efn-lg|name=picard}}\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01465-X}}\n|-\n|3\n|''The Mist''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Deep Space Nine}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Dean Wesley Smith and Kristine Kathryn Rusch{{Efn-lg|name=sisko}}\n|July 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01471-4}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Fire Ship''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Voyager}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Diane Carey{{Efn-lg|name=janeway}}\n|July 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01467-6}}\n|-\n|5\n|''Once Burned''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|New Frontier}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Peter David{{Efn-lg|name=calhoun}}\n|October 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02078-1}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Where Sea Meets Sky''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Jerry Oltion{{Efn-lg|name=pike}}\n|October 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02400-0}}\n|-\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|''The Captain's Table'' (omnibus)\n|L.A. Graf, et al.{{Efn-ua|''The Captain's Table'' (2000) by L.A. Graf, Michael Jan Friedman, Dean Wesley Smith and Kristine Kathryn Rusch, Diane Carey, Peter David, Jerry Oltion.}}\n|March 2000\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-04052-9}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Dominion War'' (1998-2004) ====\n{{Anchor|The Dominion War|Dominion War}}\n'''''Star Trek: The Dominion War''''' crossover miniseries depicts events leading up to the [[Dominion War]]. The first and third novels focus on the crew of the {{USS|Enterprise|NCC-1701-E|6}}, while the second and fourth novels are novelizations of a seven-episode arc from ''Deep Space Nine''{{'s}} sixth and seventh seasons. The novels contain additional characters and situations created by the authors.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Bowde