hed as ebook exclusives by Pocket Star.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.startrek.com/article/the-returned-out-this-summer|title=The Returned: Out This Summer|date=2015-03-07|website=StarTrek.com|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title \u25ca\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN (ebook)\n|-\n|''The Returned'', Part 1\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Peter David\n|July 6, 2015\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-9092-3}}\n|-\n|''The Returned'', Part 2\n|August 3, 2015\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-9093-0}}\n|-\n|''The Returned'', Part 3\n|September 7, 2015\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-9095-4}}\n|}\n\n=== Short fiction (1998\u20132016) ===\nCollections of short fiction from various series:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Editors(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Enterprise Logs''\n|Carol Greenburg\n|June 2000\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03579-7}}\n|-\n|''The Amazing Stories''\n|John J. Ordover\n|August 20, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-4915-0}}\n|-\n|''Tales of the Dominion War''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Keith DeCandido\n|August 3, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-9171-8}}\n|-\n|''Tales from the Captain's Table''\n|June 14, 2005\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-0520-2}}\n|-\n|''Seven Deadly Sins''\n|Margaret Clark\n|March 16, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-0944-1}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Strange New Worlds'' (1998\u20132016) ====\n{{Main|Star Trek: Strange New Worlds}}\n'''''Star Trek: Strange New Worlds''''' is a short story anthology series edited by Dean Wesley Smith. Each volume collected fan-submitted stories, similar to Bantam Books' ''The New Voyages'' (1976\u20131978).\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds''\n| rowspan=\"10\" |Dean Wesley Smith, ed.\n|July 1998\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-01446-3}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds II''\n|May 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02692-5}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds III''\n|May 2000\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-03652-1}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds IV''\n|May 1, 2001\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-1131-5}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds V''\n|May 28, 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-3778-0}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds VI''\n|June 17, 2003\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-6753-1}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds VII''\n|June 29, 2004\n|{{ISBNT|0-7434-8780-X}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds 8''\n|July 19, 2005\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-0345-5}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds 9''\n|August 22, 2006\n|{{ISBNT|1-4165-2048-1}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds 10''\n|July 10, 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-4438-8}}\n|-\n|''Strange New Worlds 2016'' \u25ca\n|Neil Bryant, et al.{{Efn-ua|''Strange New Worlds 2016'' (2016) by Neil Bryant, Gary Piserchio and Frank Tagader, Kelli Fitzpatrick, Chris Chaplin, Michael Turner, Nancy Debretsion, Derek Tyler Attico, Roger McCoy, John Coffren, and Kristen McQuinn.}}\n|October 3, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-6158-2}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Corps of Engineers'' (2000\u20132010) ===\n{{Anchor|Starfleet Corps of Engineers|Corps of Engineers|SCE|S.C.E.}}\n'''''Star Trek: Corps of Engineers''''' follows the crew of the {{Ship|USS|da Vinci|NCC-81623|6|wl=no}}. The series was marketed as ebook exclusives on various platforms, and were later collected into print bind-ups with similar titles, but a different numbering scheme.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://unreality-sf.net/2010/10/10/miracle-workers-remembering-sce-3/|title=Roundtable: Miracle Workers \u2013 remembering S.C.E. (Part 3)|last=Deffner|first=Jens|date=2010-10-10|website=unreality-sf.net|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref> The series was originally published as '''''Star Trek: Starfleet Corps of Engineers'''''.\n\n==== Original novellas (2000\u20132006) ====\nNovellas are numbered 1 through 66. Many were also published as part of multipart series, such as ''Foundations'' (2002), ''Wildfire'' (2003), and ''What's Past'' (2006). All novellas were later collected in omnibus editions with a different numbering scheme. The series name was abbreviated as '''''S.C.E.''''' on the digital covers.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title \u25ca\u2021\n!Author(s)\n!Date{{Efn|name=streetdate}}\n!ISBN (ebook)\n|-\n|1\n|''The Belly of the Beast''\n|Dean Wesley Smith\n|August 8, 