ad Universes'' (2008\u20132010) ===\n{{Anchor|Myriad Universes}}\n'''''Star Trek: Myriad Universes''''' novella series explores alternate realties, and how those settings affect the analogues of characters from various television series and films. The novellas are collected in three numbered volumes. ''The Last Generation'' comics miniseries, by Andrew Steven Harris and published by [[IDW Publishing|IDW]] from 2008 to 2009, ties into ''Infinity's Prism'' (2008) and ''Echoes and Refractions'' (2008).\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Infinity's Prism''\n|William Leisner, Christopher L. Bennett, and James Swallow\n|July 22, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-7180-3}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Echoes and Refractions''\n|Geoff Trowbridge, Keith DeCandido, and Chris Roberson\n|August 12, 2008\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-7181-0}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Shattered Light''\n|David R. George III, et al.{{Efn-ua|''Shattered Light'' (''{{Teal|Myriad Universes}}'', Book 3) (2010) by David R. George II, Steve Mollman and Michael Schuster, and Scott Pearson.}}\n|December 14, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-4841-9}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Kelvin'' Timeline (2009\u20132013) ===\n[[File:Star Trek movie logo.svg|thumb|alt=Star Trek (2009) logo.]]\nBased on ''[[Star Trek (film)|Star Trek]]'' (2009) film and its sequels.\n\n==== Film novelizations (2009\u20132013) ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Star Trek''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Alan Dean Foster\n|May 12, 2009\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-5886-9}}\n|-\n|''Star Trek Into Darkness''\n|May 21, 2013\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-1648-0}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Starfleet Academy'' (2010\u20132012) ====\n'''''Star Trek: Starfleet Academy''''' young adult miniseries explores the lives of the ''Enterprise'' crew as [[Starfleet Academy]] cadets. The series depicts the timeline of events from the ''Kelvin'' Timeline films, and differs greatly from a similarly named series published in 1996.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title \u2020\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''The Delta Anomaly''\n|Rick Barba\n|November 2, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4424-1409-9}}\n|-\n|2\n|''The Edge''\n|Rudy Josephs\n|December 28, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4424-1408-2}}\n|-\n|3\n|''The Gemini Agent''\n|Rick Barba\n|June 28, 2011\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4424-1961-2}}\n|-\n|4\n|''The Assassination Game''\n|Alan Gratz and Rick Barba\n|June 26, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4424-2058-8}}\n|}\n\n==== Original novels (2020) ====\nThe following novels were announced at the ''Star Trek'' Las Vegas 2019 convention.<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite web|url=http://blog.trekcore.com/2019/08/2020-star-trek-book-news-star-trek-picard-kelvin-timeline/|title=STAR TREK: PICARD and Kelvin Timeline Tie-In Books Lead 2020 Trek Publishing Announcements|date=2019-08-01|website=TrekCore.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-13}}</ref> They were previously scheduled for release in 2010.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://trekmovie.com/2010/01/14/pocket-books-holding-off-on-star-trek-movie-tie-ins-4-novels-pulled-from-summer-2010/|title=Pocket Books 'Holding Off' On Star Trek Movie Tie-ins \u2013 4 Novels Pulled From Summer 2010|last=Pascale|first=Anthony|date=2010-01-14|website=TrekMovie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Unsettling Stars''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|''The Unsettling Stars'' (2020), by Alan Dean Foster, was previously marketed as ''Refugees'' and ''The Order of Peace''.|name=unsettling}} (forthcoming)\n|Alan Dean Foster\n|April 14, 2020<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite book|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/The-Unsettling-Stars/Alan-Dean-Foster/Star-Trek/9781982140601|title=The Unsettling Stars|last=Foster|first=Alan Dean|date=2020-04-14|publisher=[[Pocket Books]]|isbn=9781982140601|series=Star Trek|location=New York|language=en|author-link=Alan Dean Foster|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-4060-1}}\n|-\n|''More Beautiful Than Death'' (forthcoming)\n|David Mack\n|August 11, 2020<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/9781982140625|title=More Beautiful Than Death|last=Mack|first=David|date=2020-08-11|publisher=[[Pocket Books| Pocket Books/Star Trek]]|isbn=9781982140625|series=Star Trek|location=New York|language=en|author-link=David Alan Mack|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-4062-5}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Star Trek Online'' (2010) ===\n'''''Star Trek Online''''' is based on the [[Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] [[Star Trek Online|of the same name]]. ''The Needs of the Many'' (2010), by [[Michael A. Martin]], expanded on the timeline of the events explored by players of the game. It is unclear if additional novels will be published.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Needs of the Many''\n|Michael A. Martin\n|March 30, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-8657-2}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Typhon Pact'' (2010\u20132013) ===\n{{Main|Star Trek: Typhon Pact}}\n'''''Star Trek: Typhon Pact''''' series explores the political chaos following the destruction of the Borg in ''Destiny'' (2008). ''A Singular Destiny'' (2009), by Keith DeCandido, introduced the Typhon Pact as the Federation's primary antagonist. Many storylines conclude in ''The Fall'' (2013\u201314). The novels are numbered by Simon & Schuster.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Zero Sum Game''\n|David Mack\n|October 26, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-6079-4}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Seize the Fire''\n|Michael A. Martin\n|November 30, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-6782-3}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Rough Beasts of Empire''\n|David R. George III\n|December 28, 2010\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-6081-7}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Paths of Disharmony''\n|Dayton Ward\n|January 25, 2011\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-6083-1}}\n|-\n|5\n|''The Struggle Within'' \u25ca\n|Christopher L. Bennett\n|October 4, 2011\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-5142-3}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Plagues of Night'' \u2021\n| rowspan=\"2\" |David R. George III\n|May 29, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-4955-0}}\n|-\n|7\n|''Raise the Dawn'' \u2021\n|June 26, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-4956-7}}\n|-\n|8\n|''Brinkmanship'' \u2021\n|Una McCormack\n|September 25, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-8782-8}}\n|-\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|''The Khitomer Accords Saga'' \u25ca (omnibus){{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Typhon Pact}}'', Books 6{{Snd}}8)}}\n|David R. George III and Una McCormack\n|January 22, 2013\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-3334-0}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Department of Temporal Investigations'' (2011\u20132017) ===\n{{Anchor|Department of Temporal Investigations|DTI}}\n'''''Star Trek: Department of Temporal Investigations''''', often abbreviated as '''''D.T.I.''''', is based on the fictional Federation agency responsible for investigating time travel incidents. The protagonists, Lucsly and Dulmur, were introduced in the ''Deep Space Nine'' episode \"[[Trials and Tribble-ations]]\". The novels are not numbered. ''Forgotten History'' (2012) was collected in ''The Continuing Missions'', {{Abbr|Vol.|Volume}} 1{{Efn-lr|name=continuing}} (2013).\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''Watching the Clock''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Christopher L. Bennett\n|April 26, 2011\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-0625-6}}\n|-\n|''Forgotten History'' \u2021\n|April 24, 2012\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4516-5725-8}}\n|-\n|''The Collectors'' \u25ca\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Christopher L. Bennett\n|December 8, 2014\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4767-8259-1}}\n|-\n|''Time Lock'' \u25ca\n|December 5, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-2334-4}}\n|-\n|''Shield of the Gods'' \u25ca\n|June 9, 2017\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-6488-0}}\n|}\n\n=== ''The Fall'' (2013\u201314) ===\n{{Anchor|The Fall}}\n'''''Star Trek: The Fall''''' is a continuation of ''Typhon Pact'' (2010\u20132013). Events in the novels occur over a two-month period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://trekcore.com/blog/2013/09/exclusive-una-mccormack-interview/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Una McCormack Interview|date=2013-09-18|website=trekcore.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-30}}</ref>\n{|