4767-5308-9}}\n|-\n|''Control''\n|March 28, 2017\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-5170-5}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Prey'' (2016) ===\n'''''Star Trek: Prey''''' follows the exploits of a company of thieves. Includes characters from ''Star Trek'', ''Next Generation'', and ''Titan''. Written by [[John Jackson Miller]].\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Hell's Heart''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |John Jackson Miller\n|September 27, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-1579-0}}\n|-\n|2\n|''The Jackal's Trick''\n|October 25, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-1580-6}}\n|-\n|3\n|''The Hall of Heroes''\n|November 29, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-1603-2}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Discovery'' (2017\u2013present) ===\n{{Main|Star Trek: Discovery#Novels}}\n[[File:Star Trek Discovery logo.svg|thumb|alt=Star Trek: Discovery logo.]]\n'''''Star Trek: Discovery''''' book line is based on the [[Star Trek: Discovery|television series of the same name]], with each volume following the continuity of the television series closely.<ref>{{Cite podcast|url=http://www.trek.fm/literary-treks/206|title=Almost Too Much Latitude|website=Literary Treks|number=206|publisher=Trek.fm|date=2017-10-08|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref> The novels are numbered by Simon & Schuster; however, not all printings include a number stamp.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite book|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/9781982113315|title=The Enterprise War|last=Miller|first=John Jackson|date=2019-07-30|publisher=[[Pocket Books|Pocket Books/Star Trek]]|isbn=9781982113315|series=Star Trek: Discovery|volume=5|location=New York|language=en|author-link=John Jackson Miller|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Desperate Hours''\n|David Mack\n|September 26, 2017\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-6457-6}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Drastic Measures''\n|Dayton Ward\n|February 6, 2018\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-7174-1}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Fear Itself''\n|James Swallow\n|June 5, 2018\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-5011-6659-4}}\n|-\n|4\n|''The Way to the Stars''\n|Una McCormack\n|January 8, 2019\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-0475-7}}\n|-\n|5\n|''The Enterprise War''\n|John Jackson Miller\n|July 30, 2019\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-1331-5}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Dead Endless''\n|Dave Galanter\n|December 17, 2019\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-2384-0}}\n|-\n|7\n|''Die Standing'' (forthcoming)\n|John Jackson Miller\n|July 14, 2020<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite book|last=Miller|first=John Jackson|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/9781982136291|title=Die Standing|date=2020-07-14|publisher=[[Pocket Books|Pocket Books/Star Trek]]|isbn=9781982136291|series=Star Trek: Discovery|volume=7|location=New York|language=en|author-link=John Jackson Miller|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-3629-1}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Picard'' (2020) ===\n[[File:Star Trek Picard logo.svg|thumb|alt=Star Trek: Picard logo.]]\n'''''Star Trek: Picard''''' is based on the [[Star Trek: Picard|television series of the same name]]. ''The Last Best Hope'' (2020) is a prequel to the television series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.startrek.com/news/new-star-trek-books-simon-schuster-discovery-idw|title=New 'Picard' Prequel Books Revealed at STLV Publishing Panel|date=2019-08-01|website=Star Trek|language=en|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Last Best Hope''\n|Una McCormack\n|February 11, 2020<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.simonandschuster.com/books/9781982139445|title=The Last Best Hope|last=McCormack|first=Una|date=2020-02-11|publisher=[[Pocket Books|Pocket Books/Star Trek]]|isbn=9781982139445|series=Star Trek: Picard|location=New York|language=en|author-link=Una McCormack|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-9821-3944-5}}\n|}\n\n== Titan Books (1987\u2013present) ==\n{{Anchor|Titan Books}}\nA division of the [[Titan Publishing Group]], Titan Books reprinted Pocket and Bantam Books originals for the United Kingdom market from 1987 to 1995. [[Penguin Random House]] distributes Titan's licensed publications to the United States and Canada. Outside of North America, Titan's reprints are the most widely available editions. Many reprints include spelling changes and minor corrections to their original text to align with Titan's house style, and with [[British spelling]].\n\n=== ''Star Trek'' (reprint) (1987\u20131993) ===\nReprints of Pocket Book's '''''Star Trek''''' novels with a different number scheme:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Chain of Attack''\n|Gene DeWeese\n|March 1987\n|{{ISBNT|0-907610-85-4}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Deep Domain''\n|Howard Weinstein\n|June 1987\n|{{ISBNT|0-907610-86-2}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Dreams of the Raven''\n|Carmen Carter\n|July 1987\n|{{ISBNT|0-907610-93-5}}\n|-\n|4\n|''The Romulan Way''\n|Diane Duane and Peter Morwood\n|August 1987\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-002-2}}\n|-\n|5\n|''How Much for Just the Planet?''\n|John M. Ford\n|October 1987\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-018-9}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Bloodthirst''\n|J. M. Dillard\n|December 1987\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-039-1}}\n|-\n|7\n|''The I.D.I.C. Epidemic''\n|Jean Lorrah\n|February 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-042-1}}\n|-\n|8\n|''Yesterday's Son''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |A. C. Crispin\n|March 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-061-8}}\n|-\n|9\n|''Time for Yesterday''\n|April 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-063-4}}\n|-\n|10\n|''The Final Reflection''\n|John M. Ford\n|May 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-064-2}}\n|-\n|11\n|''Time Trap''\n|David Dvorkin\n|June 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-065-0}}\n|-\n|12\n|''The Vulcan Academy Murders''\n|Jean Lorrah\n|July 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-066-9}}\n|-\n|13\n|''The Three-Minute Universe''\n|Barbara Paul\n|August 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-068-5}}\n|-\n|14\n|''Star Trek: The Motion Picture'' (novelization)\n|Gene Roddenberry\n| rowspan=\"2\" |September 1988\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-069-3}}\n|-\n|15\n|''The Wrath of Khan'' (novelization)\n|Vonda N. McIntyre\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-071-5}}\n|-\n|16\n|''Memory Prime''\n|Judith and Garfield Reeves-Stevens\n|October 1988\n|{{I