-1}}\n|-\n|59\n|''The Starship Trap''\n|Mel Gilden\n|March 19, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-460-5}}\n|-\n|60\n|''Windos on a Lost World''\n|V.E. Mitchell\n|May 25, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-461-3}}\n|-\n|61\n|''From the Depths''\n|Victor Milan\n|August 5, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-467-2}}\n|-\n|62\n|''The Great Starship Race''\n|Diane Carey\n|September 30, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-489-3}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Star Trek'' Giant Novel (1987\u20131990) ===\nReprints of select original novels; each marketed as a \"''Star Trek'' Giant Novel\", featuring cover art and design by [[Boris Vallejo]]. The novels are numbered, but not all printings include a number stamp.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Enterprise: The First Voyage'' (unpublished)\n|Vonda N. McIntyre\n|''September 1987''\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|-\n|2\n|''Strangers from the Sky''\n|Margaret Wander Bonanno\n|October 1987\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-008-1}}\n|-\n|3\n|''Uhura's Song''\n|Janet Kagan\n|May 1989\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-184-3}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Dwellers in the Crucible''\n|Margaret Wander Bonanno\n|September 1989\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-206-8}}\n|-\n|5\n|''Shadow Lord''\n|Laurence Yep\n|April 1990\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-287-4}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Pawns and Symbols''\n|Majliss Larson\n|September 27, 1990\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-323-4}}\n|}\nUntil 2011, [[Nielsen BookScan|BookScan]] provided an incomplete record for the ''Enterprise: The First Voyage'' reprint, originally scheduled for a September 1987 release, which was withdrawn for unknown reasons. ''Vendetta'' (1991), by Peter David, was marketed as a \"Giant Novel\" in North America, but it is not part of this series. Bookseller platforms in the United Kingdom have erroneously linked ''Vendetta''{{'s}} Simon & Schuster, Ltd. (UK) publication to Titan's reprints.\n\n=== ''New Voyages'' (reprint) (1992) ===\nReprints of '''''Star Trek: The New Voyages''''' anthology series edited by Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath. Some printings include significant spelling corrections and unexplained prose changes.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Editors(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The New Voyages''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath\n|August 27, 1992\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-448-6}}\n|-\n|''The New Voyages 2''\n|December 16, 1992\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-453-2}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Star Trek Adventures'' (1993\u20131995) ===\n{{Anchor|Star Trek Adventures}}\nBantam Book's original novels reprinted by Titan as '''''Star Trek Adventures'''''. The series name has since been erroneously applied to the Bantam editions by book discovery websites. The novels are numbered by Titan, and include significant corrections and spelling changes. Not all printings include a number stamp.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''The Galactic Whirlpool''\n|David Gerrold\n|June 29, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-486-9}}\n|-\n|2\n|''The Price of the Phoenix''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|name=spelling}}\n|Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath\n|November 1, 1993\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-504-0}}\n|-\n|3\n|''The Starless World''\n|Gordon Eklund\n|January 27, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-505-9}}\n|-\n|4\n|''Perry's Planet''\n|Jack C. Haldeman, II.\n|February 24, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-509-1}}\n|-\n|5\n|''Mudd's Angels'' (anthology)\n|J. A. Lawrence\n|April 14, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-510-5}}\n|-\n|6\n|''Trek to Madworld''\n|Stephen Goldin\n|June 23, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-530-X}}\n|-\n|7\n|''Planet of Judgment''\n|Joe Haldeman\n|August 11, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-531-8}}\n|-\n|8\n|''Devil World''\n|Gordon Eklund\n|October 20, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-532-6}}\n|-\n|9\n|''The Fate of the Phoenix''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|name=spelling}}\n|Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath\n|December 15, 1994\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-535-0}}\n|-\n|10\n|''Death's Angel''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Kathleen Sky\n|February 16, 1995\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-536-9}}\n|-\n|11\n|''Vulcan!''\n|April 20, 1995\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-537-7}}\n|-\n|12\n|''World Without End''\n|Joe Haldeman\n|June 22, 1995\n|{{ISBNT|1-85286-538-5}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Prometheus'' (English edition) (2017\u201318) ===\nEnglish edition of '''''Star Trek: Prometheus''''', a German-language flagship concept series written by Christian Humberg and Bernd Perplies. Originally published by Cross Cult as part of ''Star Trek''{{'s}} 50th Anniversary celebration.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite podcast|url=http://www.trek.fm/literary-treks/253|title=Basically Watching the News Frankly|publisher=Trek.fm|website=Literary Treks|date=2017-12-31|number=253|access-date=2019-03-06}}</ref> The English editions were translated by Helga Parmiter, and edited by [[Keith DeCandido]].<ref>{{Cite podcast|url=http://www.trek.fm/literary-treks/214|title=A Pair of Richards|publisher=Trek.fm|website=Literary Treks|date=2017-12-31|number=214|access-date=2018-01-01}}</ref> Not all printings include a number stamp.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|''Fire with Fire''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Christian Humberg and Bernd Perplies,{{Indent|2}}Helga Parmiter, translator\n|November 28, 2017\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-78565-649-1}}\n|-\n|2\n|''The Root of All Rage''\n|May 29, 2018\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-78565-651-4}}\n|-\n|3\n|''In the Heart of Chaos''\n|November 27, 2018\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-78565-653-8}}\n|}\n\n== Other licensed works ==\nBelow is an incomplete list of licensed works from other publishers:\n\n=== ''Mission to Horatius'' (1968\u20131999) ===\n{{Main|Mission to Horatius}}\n''Star Trek: Mission to Horatius'' (1968) is a young adult novel written by [[Mack Reynolds]]. It was the first original novel to be based on the [[Star Trek: The Original Series|television series]], and the only novel to be published while the series aired on [[NBC]]. Published by [[Western Publishing|Whitman Books]] as part of a book line based on popular television properties.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Star Trek Creator: The Authorized Biography of Gene Roddenberry|last=Alexander|first=David|date=June 1994|publisher=[[Roc Books]]|isbn=9780451454188|location=New York|pages=[https://archive.org/details/startrekcreatora00alex/page/339 339]|url=https://archive.org/details/startrekcreatora00alex/page/339}}</ref> A facsimile reproduction was published by Pocket Books in 1999.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title \u2020^\n!Author(s)\n!Publisher\n!Date\n!Catalog{{\\}}ISBN\n|-\n|''Mission to Horatius''\n|Mack Reynolds\n|Whitman Books\n|November 1968\n|1549\n|-\n|''Mission to Horatius'' (reprint)\n|Mack Reynolds and John Ordover, ed.\n|Pocket Books\n|February 1999\n|{{ISBNT|0-671-02812-X}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Star Trek Reader'' (1976\u20131978) ===\n'''''The Star Trek Reader''''' is a four-volume, limited-edition, collection of Jame's Blish's episode novelizations. The novel ''[[Spock Must Die!]]'' was included. Published by [[E. P. Dutton]]. Variants were made available to the Science Fiction Book Club from 1976 to 1979.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/pe.cgi?38120|title=Series: The Star Trek Reader|website=[[ISFDB]]|access-date=2019-07-30}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title \u2020\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Star Trek Reader''\n| rowspan=\"4\" |James Blish\n|October 1976\n|{{ISBNT|0-8415-0467-9}}\n|-\n|''The Star Trek Reader II''\n|April 1977\n|{{ISBNT|0-525-20960-3}}\n|-\n|''The Star Trek Reader III''\n|September 1977\n|{{ISBNT|0-525-20961-1}}\n|-\n|''The Star Trek Reader IV''\n|March 1978\n|{{ISBNT|0-525-20962-X}}\n|}\n\n=== Science Fiction Book Club (1998\u20132007) ===\n{{Anchor|Science Fiction Book Club|SFBC}}\nThe [[Bookspan|Science Fiction Book Club]], in partnership with Doubleday, has published omnibus editions of various miniseries available exclusively to club members. Variants intended for libraries are also known to exist. Below is an incomplete list:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title \u2020\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''New Frontier''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|New Frontier}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}4)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Peter David\n|January 1998\n|{{ISBNT|1-56865-502-9}}\n|-\n|''Prometheans''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|New Frontier}}'', Books 5{{Snd}}6)}}\n|July 1998\n|{{ISBNT|1-56865-742-0}}\n|-\n|''The Q Continuum''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Q Continuum}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}3)}}\n|Greg Cox\n|November 1998\n|{{ISBNT|1-56865-954-7}}\n|-\n|''Rihannsu''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|Rihannsu}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}4)}}\n|Diane Duane and Peter Morwood\n|October 2000\n|{{ISBNT|0-7394-1390-2}}\n|-\n|''The Genesis Wave''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Genesis Wave}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}2)}}\n|John Vornholt\n|June 2001\n|{{ISBNT|0-7394-1843-2}}\n|-\n|''Stargazer''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Stargazer}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}2)}}\n|Michael Jan Friedman\n|June 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7394-2617-6}}\n|-\n|''The Janus Gate''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Janus Gate}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}2)}}\n|L.A. Graf\n|October 2002\n|{{ISBNT|0-7394-2854-3}}\n|-\n|''Vulcan's Soul''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{NavyC|The Vulcan's Soul}}'', Books 1{{Snd}}3)}}\n|Josepha Sherman and Susan Shwartz\n|April 2007\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-7394-8205-6}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Classic Episodes'' (2016) ===\n''Star Trek: The Classic Episodes'' is an omnibus edition of episode novelizations by Blish and Lawrence originally published by Bantam Books. Published by [[Barnes & Noble]] as part of the ''Collectible Editions'' series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/star-trek-james-blish/1122539370?ean=9780385365246|title=Star Trek: The Classic Episodes (Barnes & Noble Collectible Editions)|date=2016-04-29|website=[[Barnes & Noble]]|language=en|access-date=2019-08-31}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Author\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|''The Classic Episodes'' \u2020 (omnibus)\n|James Blish and J. A. Lawrence\n|April 29, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-0-385-36524-6}}\n|}\n\n=== ''Prometheus'' (German edition) (2016) ===\n'''''Star Trek: Prometheus''''' is a German-language flagship concept series written by Christian Humberg and Bernd Perplies. Published by Cross Cult as part of ''Star Trek''{{'s}} 50th Anniversary celebration.<ref name=\":8\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!ISBN\n|-\n|1\n|{{Lang|de|Feuer gegen Feuer}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Christian Humberg and Bernd Perplies\n|July 29, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-3-86425-851-0}}\n|-\n|2\n|{{Lang|de|Der Ursprung allen Zorns}}\n|August 22, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-3-86425-852-7}}\n|-\n|3\n|{{Lang|de|Ins Herz des Chaos}}\n|September 19, 2016\n|{{ISBNT|978-3-86425-853-4}}\n|}\n\n== Unpublished novels ==\nBelow is an incomplete list of unpublished ''Star Trek'' novels:\n\n=== Bantam Books (1978\u20131981) ===\nThe following is a list of unpublished novels previously attributed to Bantam Books:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Tentative Title\n!Author(s)\n!Date\n!Ref(s)\n|-\n|''Uhura!''{{Hsp}}\n|Nichelle Nichols,{{Indent|2}}with Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''1979\u20131981''\n|<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.well.com/~sjroby/lostbooks.html|title=Complete Starfleet Library - Star Trek: The Lost Books|last=Roby|first=Steven J.|website=www.well.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210174617/http://www.well.com/~sjroby/lostbooks.html|archive-date=February 10, 2015|access-date=2018-12-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|''The New Voyages 3{{Snd}}4''\n|Sondra Marshak and Myrna Culbreath, ed.\n|<ref name=\":11\" />\n|-\n|''The Harlequin Game''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|''The Harlequin Game'' (''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}}, an unpublished novel by Steven E. McDonald, is also known as ''Harlequin''.}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Steven E. McDonald\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''1980\u201381''\n| rowspan=\"3\" |<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n|''Mirrorgates''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|''Mirrorgates'' (''{{Teal|Star Trek}}''{{--)}}, an unpublished novel by Steven E. McDonald, is also known as ''Mirror Gates'' and ''Gates''.}}\n|-\n|''Moonchild''\n|}\n\n=== Simon & Schuster (1979\u20132014) ===\nThe following is a list of unpublished novels attributed to Simon & Schuster:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Tentative Title\n!Author(s)\n!Schedul