nded''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|Deep Space Nine}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Bradley Thompson\n|''2001\u20132005''\n| rowspan=\"6\" {{Unknown|}}\n|<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n|''Gateways'' \u2020 (omnibus)\n|John J. Ordover, ed.\n|''2001\u20132005''\n|{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n|-\n|''Harm's Way'', Books 1{{Snd}}3\n|Jerry Oltion and Kathy Oltion\n|''2002\u20132003''\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.trektoday.com/news/210701_04.shtml|title=Packed Pocket Books Schedule For 2002|last=Caillan|date=2001-02-21|website=www.trektoday.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Tzenkethi War'' (anthology){{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Lost Era}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Marco Palmieri, ed.\n|''2003\u20132007''\n|{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n|-\n|''A Time to Create''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Dafydd ab Hugh\n|''August 2004''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|''A Time to Destroy''\n|''September 2004''\n|-\n|''Crucible'' \u2020 (omnibus)\n|David R. George III\n|''May 5, 2009''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-0248-0}}\n|\n|-\n|''Millennium Bloom''{{Indent|2}}{{Small|(''{{Teal|The Next Generation}}''{{--)}}}}\n|Mike W. Barr\n|''2010\u201311''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-0220-6}}\n|\n|}\n\n==== ''Academy'' (2008\u20132019) ====\n''Trial Run'' (2008) was announced as the second novel of a new flagship series, ''Star Trek: Academy'', to follow the exploits of a young Midshipman Jim Kirk.<ref name=\":2\" /> A new novel, ''Third Class'', appeared on bookseller platforms sometime in 2018, scheduled for a December 2019 release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bookdepository.com/Third-Class-William-Shatner/9781416503996|title=Third Class : William Shatner : 9781416503996|website=[[Book Depository]]|access-date=2019-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.waterstones.com/book/third-class/william-shatner/judith-reeves-stevens/9781416503996|title=Third Class by William Shatner, Judith Reeves-Stevens|website=[[Waterstones]]|language=en|access-date=2019-03-12}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Tentative Title\n!Author(s)\n!Scheduled\n!Known ISBN{{Efn|name=knownisbn}}\n|-\n|''Trial Run''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |William Shatner,{{Indent|2}}with Judith and Garfield Reeves-Stevens\n|''2008\u20132010''\n|{{Unknown|}}\n|-\n|''Third Class''\n|''December 31, 2019''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-0399-6}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Kelvin'' Timeline (2010) ====\nNovels based on the ''Kelvin'' Timeline [[List of Star Trek films and television series#Reboot (Kelvin Timeline) films|film series]] which were withdrawn from publication.<ref name=\":5\" /> The titles reappeared on bookseller platforms in 2011, and again in 2014. At the ''Star Trek'' Las Vegas 2019 convention, ''More Beautiful Than Death'' and ''Refugees'' were announced as scheduled for publication in 2020.<ref name=\":14\" /> ''Refugees'' was retitled ''The Order of Peace'' in initial promotional materials, however, the finished novel will be published as ''The Unsettling Stars'' in 2020.<ref name=\":4\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Tentative Title\n!Author(s)\n!Scheduled\n!Known ISBN{{Efn|name=knownisbn}}\n|-\n|''Refugees''{{Hsp}}{{Efn|name=unsettling}}\n|Alan Dean Foster\n|''April 27, 2010''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-7553-8}}\n|-\n|''Seek A Newer World''\n|Christopher L. Bennett\n|''May 25, 2010''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4165-9816-9}}\n|-\n|''More Beautiful Than Death''\n|David Mack\n|''June 29, 2010''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-7668-9}}\n|-\n|''The Hazard of Concealing''\n|Greg Cox\n|''July 27, 2010''\n|{{ISBNT|978-1-4391-8414-1}}\n|}\n\n==== ''Orion Factor'' (2010\u20132014) ====\n{{Anchor|The Orion Factor|Orion Factor}}\n'''''Star Trek: The Orion Factor''''' miniseries first appeared on bookseller platforms sometime in 2009. The novels were listed as forthcoming in 2010, and again in 2012, before being withdrawn in 2014. The [[Books In Print]] electronic version includes an incomplete record for ''Song of Experience''. The series remains unpublished.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Tentative Title\n!Author\n!Scheduled\n!Known 