alta]], [[Menorca Airport|Menorca]], [[Odessa International Airport|Odessa]], [[Olbia Costa Smeralda Airport|Olbia]], [[Palma de Mallorca Airport|Palma de Mallorca]], [[Poprad-Tatry Airport|Poprad-Tatry]], [[Keflav\u00edk International Airport|Reykjav\u00edk\u2013Keflav\u00edk]], [[Rhodes International Airport|Rhodes]], [[Rijeka Airport|Rijeka]], [[Salzburg Airport|Salzburg]], [[Sochi International Airport|Sochi]], [[Split Airport|Split]], [[Stavanger Airport|Stavanger]], [[Thessaloniki Airport|Thessaloniki]], [[Venice Marco Polo Airport|Venice]], [[Verona Villafranca Airport|Verona]] <br>'''Seasonal charter:''' [[Marche Airport|Ancona]],<ref name=\"charters\">{{cite web|url=https://worldairlinenews.com/2018/05/30/airbaltic-to-operate-charter-flights-for-tez-tour-latvija/|title=airBaltic to operate charter flights for Tez Tour Latvija|publisher=worldairlinenews.com|accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref> [[Antalya Airport|Antalya]],<ref name=\"charters\"/> [[Burgas Airport|Burgas]],<ref name=\"charters\"/> [[Gran Canaria Airport|Gran Canaria]] (begins 17 October 2020),<ref name=\"TTRiga\"/> [[Heraklion International Airport|Heraklion]],<ref name=\"charters\"/> [[Hurghada International Airport|Hurghada]],<ref name=\"TTRiga\"/> [[Araxos Airport|Patras]],<ref name=\"charters\"/> [[Sharm El Sheikh International Airport|Sharm El Sheikh]]<ref name=\"TTRiga\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tez-tour.com/avia-reference.html|title=Flight Schedules and Airline Availability|website=tez-tour.com}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Belavia]] | [[Minsk National Airport|Minsk]]\n<!-- -->\n| {{nowrap|[[BRA Braathens Regional Airlines]]}} | [[Stockholm Bromma Airport|Stockholm\u2013Bromma]]<ref>{{cite news |title=BRA satsar p\u00e5 utrikesflyg: lanserar fem nya flyglinjer |url=https://via.tt.se/pressmeddelande/bra-satsar-pa-utrikesflyg-lanserar-fem-nya-flyglinjer?publisherId=3234555&releaseId=3262653 |accessdate= 9 October 2019 |work=via.tt.se |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| {{nowrap|[[Corendon Airl